{
  "texts": [
    "Motor dysfunction and sensory neuropathy occurred in 1 (0.8%) and 0 cases, respectively, with no grade 4 or 5 events.",
    "Among 119 patients who received a two-step priming dose regimen, 56.3% developed cytokine release syndrome (CRS).",
    "All CRS incidents were Level 1 (42.0%) or Level 2 (14.3%), and no level 3 or above incidents were reported.",
    "With respect to the most recent dose, the median time to onset of CRS was 2.0 days (range: 1.0-9.0 days) and the median time to resolution was 2.0 days (range: 1.0-19.0 days).",
    "Overall, 98.8% of CRS events occurred in the first three doses, and 90.6% occurred in the incremental dose."
  ]
}